ist);\r\n\r\n\nObs.: pergunta de quarta-feira (dia 17/04).'),(491,'Pergunta do dia: 975','19s1P-BecGQ','Ari Stopassola Junior','2013-04-22 09:40:30','You run the following PHP script:\r\n&lt;?php\r\nclass number {\r\n    public $a= 10;\r\n    public $b=20;\r\n    private $c=30;\r\n}\r\n$numbers = new number();\r\nforeach($numbers as $var =&gt; $value) {\r\n\n    echo \"$value \";\r\n}\r\n?&gt;\r\nWhat will be the output?\r\n\r\nA: 10 20\r\nB: 10 20 30\r\nC: 10 20 0\r\nD: The script will throw an error.\r\n\r\n\nObs.: pergunta de ontem, quinta-feira (dia 18/04).'),(492,'Pergunta do dia: 976','L8Qb_o1_iec','Ari Stopassola Junior','2013-04-22 09:40:00','Which of the following functions can be used to get whether or not a file is readable?\r\n\r\nA: is_readable()\r\nB: touch()\r\nC: stat()\r\nD: fseek()'),(493,'Pergunta do dia: 977','dFddgcefDuM','Ari Stopassola Junior','2013-04-22 09:39:41','Which of the following file functions can be used to indicate the current position of the file read/write pointer?\r\n\r\nA: fread()\r\nB: ftell()\r\nC: feof()\r\nD: fseek()\r\n\r\n\nObs.: pergunta de ontem, sábado (dia 20/04).'),(494,'Pergunta do dia: 978','czn4NGYo9y8','Ari Stopassola Junior','2013-04-22 09:39:26','Consider the following PHP script:\r\n&lt;?php\r\n$fp = fopen(\'file.txt\', \'r\');\r\n$string1 = fgets($fp, 512);\r\nfseek($fp, 0);\r\n?&gt;\r\nWhich of the following functions will give the same output as that given by the fseek() function in the above script?\r\n\r\nA: rewind()\r\nB: fgets()\r\nC: fgetss()\r\nD: file()'),(495,'Pergunta do dia: 954','kPVmjHC1TWc','Ari Stopassola Junior','2013-04-19 10:30:34','You want to search for such users who have not used any digit in their\n\r\nuser names to register to your Website. Which of the following regular\n\r\nexpressions will you use to accomplish the task?\n\r\n\r\nA: [[:digit:^]]\n\r\nB: [^[:digit:]]\n\r\nC: ^[[:digit]]\n\r\nD: [[:digit:]^]\n\r\n\r\nDetalhe: essa pergunta aborda o estilo POSIX de expressões regulares,\n\r\nportanto não cai na versão 5.3 do exame.\n\r\nDe qualquer forma, é interessante recapitular os conceitos. RegExp é\n\r\nsempre importante ter em mente...\n\r\n\r\nObs.: pergunta de quinta-feira (dia 28/03).'),(496,'Pergunta do dia: 955','wu-BkpH-hOs','Ari Stopassola Junior','2013-04-19 10:29:50','Consider the following array:\n\r\n$arr = array(\'apple\', \'banana\', \'cherry\');\n\r\nYou want to put this array into the following form: apple, banana, cherry\n\r\nWhich of the following functions will you use to accomplish the task\n\r\ninto a single call?\n\r\n\r\nA: implode()\n\r\nB: explode()\n\r\nC: ltrim()\n\r\nD: substr()\n\r\n\r\nObs.: pergunta de ontem, sexta-feira (dia 29/03).'),(497,'Pergunta do dia: 956','Ue8QRTHpsOs','Ari Stopassola Junior','2013-04-19 10:29:12','The dl() function is used to load PHP extensions on the server at\n\r\nruntime. However, you want to disable it due to some security issue.\n\r\nWhich of the following actions will you perform to accomplish the\n\r\ntask?\n\r\n\r\nA: Set the enable_dl option to 0 in the PHP.ini file.\n\r\nB: Add the dl() function in the blocked_functions() list in the PHP.ini file.\n\r\nC: Add the dl() function in the disable_functions list in the PHP.ini\n\r\nconfiguration file.\n\r\nD: Set the enable_dl option to 1 in the PHP.ini file.'),(498,'Pergunta do dia: 957','w-9mOFX2rxM','Ari Stopassola Junior','2013-04-19 10:28:49','You have given the following XML data in the tasks.XML file:\n\r\n&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"ISO-8859-1\"?&gt;\n\r\n&lt;tasklist&gt;\n\r\n&lt;note&gt;\n\r\n&lt;tasks&gt;Validate data&lt;/tasks&gt;\n\r\n&lt;details&gt;String Validation&lt;/details&gt;\n\r\n&lt;/note&gt;\n\r\n&lt;note&gt;\n\r\n&lt;tasks&gt;Secure data&lt;/tasks&gt;\n\r\n&lt;details&gt;Encryption&lt;/details&gt;\n\r\n&lt;/note&gt;\n\r\n&lt;/tasklist&gt;\n\r\n\r\nNow, you run the following PHP script:\n\r\n\r\n&lt;?php\n\r\n$objDOM = new DOMDocument();\n\r\n$objDOM-&gt;load(\"tasks.xml\");\n\r\n$note = $objDOM-&g